Reasoning: The paper deals with the continuity of various channel parameters and operations, which are primarily studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the topologies on the space of equivalent DMC, which falls under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the study of probability of error of a fixed code and optimal probability of error for a given code rate and block length, which are related to coding theory (cs.ITP). The paper also discusses channel operations such as sums, products, interpolations, and Arikan-style transformations, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and data structures (cs.DS).
